Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula is updating the country on changes to seaport access. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula has updated the country on changes to sea ports access. Some of the country's ports of entry are being closed to curb the spread of coronovirus. There have been 116 COVID-19 cases in South Africa so far. Gauteng has the highest number of new coronavirus cases. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? So far South Africa has not reported any death from the coronavirus which has claimed the lives of nearly 8,000 people worldwide. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.